The roots of \( P(x) \) are \( x = 1, 2, 3, \ldots, 10 \) with multiplicities 1, 2, 3,..., 10 respectively. 1. **Leading Term Analysis**: The leading term of \( P(x) \) is \( x^{1+2+3+\cdots+10} = x^{55} \). Since 55 is odd, \( P(x) \) tends to \( +\infty \) as \( x \to +\infty \) and \( -\infty \) as \( x \to -\infty \). 2. **Sign Changes at Roots**: - For each root \( x = k \), if the multiplicity is odd, the sign of \( P(x) \) changes as we pass through \( x = k \). - If the multiplicity is even, the sign remains the same. 3. **Sign Analysis**: - Starting from \( x < 1 \), all factors \( (x - k) \) are negative. The product of these terms with even multiplicities is positive, and with odd multiplicities is negative. The total sign is determined by the product of \( (-1)^k \) for \( k \) from 1 to 10, which is \( (-1)^{55} = -1 \). Thus, \( P(x) \) is negative for \( x < 1 \). - Crossing each root \( x = k \): - Odd multiplicities (1, 3, 5, 7, 9) flip the sign. - Even multiplicities (2, 4, 6, 8, 10) do not flip the sign. 4. **Interval Sign Determination**: - \( (-\infty, 1) \): Negative - \( (1, 2) \): Positive (flip at \( x = 1 \)) - \( (2, 3) \): Positive (even multiplicity at \( x = 2 \)) - \( (3, 4) \): Negative (flip at \( x = 3 \)) - \( (4, 5) \): Negative (even multiplicity at \( x = 4 \)) - \( (5, 6) \): Positive (flip at \( x = 5 \)) - \( (6, 7) \): Positive (even multiplicity at \( x = 6 \)) - \( (7, 8) \): Negative (flip at \( x = 7 \)) - \( (8, 9) \): Negative (even multiplicity at \( x = 8 \)) - \( (9, 10) \): Positive (flip at \( x = 9 \)) - \( (10, \infty) \): Positive (even multiplicity at \( x = 10 \)) The intervals where \( P(x) \) is positive are \( (1, 2) \), \( (2, 3) \), \( (5, 6) \), \( (6, 7) \), \( (9, 10) \), and \( (10, \infty) \).
